		<header>
				<h1 class=3D"entry-title">
			Module 21: Converting Units of Area		</h1>
										</header>
		<div>
<p><span style=3D"color: #ff6600"><strong>You may use a calculator througho=
ut this module.</strong></span></p>
<p>Converting between units of area requires us to be careful because squar=
e units behave differently than linear units.</p>
<h1><strong><em>U.S. System: Converting Measurements of Area</em></strong><=
/h1>
<p><img decoding=3D"async" class=3D"size-full wp-image-169 aligncenter" src=
=3D"https://spscc.pressbooks.pub/app/uploads/sites/86/2019/12/Area-sqyd.png=
" alt=3D"a square that has sides 1 yard long" width=3D"150" height=3D"150">=
</p>
<p>Consider a square yard; the area of a square with sides <img decoding=3D=
"async" src=3D"https://spscc.pressbooks.pub/app/uploads/quicklatex/quicklat=
ex.com-69a7c7fb1023d315f416440bca10d849_l3.svg" class=3D"ql-img-inline-form=
ula quicklatex-auto-format" alt=3D"1" title=3D"Rendered by QuickLaTeX.com" =
height=3D"12" width=3D"7" style=3D"vertical-align: 0px;"> yard long.</p>
<p><img decoding=3D"async" class=3D"size-full wp-image-170 aligncenter" src=
=3D"https://spscc.pressbooks.pub/app/uploads/sites/86/2021/09/Area-sqft-sqy=
d.png" alt=3D"a 3 by 3 grid representing 9 square feet" width=3D"150" heigh=
t=3D"150"></p>
<p><img decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://spscc.pressbooks.pub/app/uploads/=
quicklatex/quicklatex.com-69a7c7fb1023d315f416440bca10d849_l3.svg" class=3D=
"ql-img-inline-formula quicklatex-auto-format" alt=3D"1" title=3D"Rendered =
by QuickLaTeX.com" height=3D"12" width=3D"7" style=3D"vertical-align: 0px;"=
> yard =3D <img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://spscc.pr=
essbooks.pub/app/uploads/quicklatex/quicklatex.com-ce2009a45822333037922ccc=
a0872a55_l3.svg" class=3D"ql-img-inline-formula quicklatex-auto-format" alt=
=3D"3" title=3D"Rendered by QuickLaTeX.com" height=3D"12" width=3D"9" style=
=3D"vertical-align: 0px;"> feet, so we can divide the square into three sec=
tions vertically and three sections horizontally to convert both dimensions=
 of the square from yards to feet. This forms a <img loading=3D"lazy" decod=
ing=3D"async" src=3D"https://spscc.pressbooks.pub/app/uploads/quicklatex/qu=
icklatex.com-ce2009a45822333037922ccca0872a55_l3.svg" class=3D"ql-img-inlin=
e-formula quicklatex-auto-format" alt=3D"3" title=3D"Rendered by QuickLaTeX=
.com" height=3D"12" width=3D"9" style=3D"vertical-align: 0px;"> by <img loa=
ding=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://spscc.pressbooks.pub/app/up=
loads/quicklatex/quicklatex.com-ce2009a45822333037922ccca0872a55_l3.svg" cl=
ass=3D"ql-img-inline-formula quicklatex-auto-format" alt=3D"3" title=3D"Ren=
dered by QuickLaTeX.com" height=3D"12" width=3D"9" style=3D"vertical-align:=
 0px;"> grid, which shows us visually that <img decoding=3D"async" src=3D"h=
ttps://spscc.pressbooks.pub/app/uploads/quicklatex/quicklatex.com-69a7c7fb1=
023d315f416440bca10d849_l3.svg" class=3D"ql-img-inline-formula quicklatex-a=
uto-format" alt=3D"1" title=3D"Rendered by QuickLaTeX.com" height=3D"12" wi=
dth=3D"7" style=3D"vertical-align: 0px;"> square yard equals <img loading=
=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://spscc.pressbooks.pub/app/upload=
s/quicklatex/quicklatex.com-824dc08b6ac6c7e5c07f1113ebaab27b_l3.svg" class=
=3D"ql-img-inline-formula quicklatex-auto-format" alt=3D"9" title=3D"Render=
ed by QuickLaTeX.com" height=3D"12" width=3D"9" style=3D"vertical-align: 0p=
x;"> square feet, not <img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https=
://spscc.pressbooks.pub/app/uploads/quicklatex/quicklatex.com-ce2009a458223=
33037922ccca0872a55_l3.svg" class=3D"ql-img-inline-formula quicklatex-auto-=
format" alt=3D"3" title=3D"Rendered by QuickLaTeX.com" height=3D"12" width=
=3D"9" style=3D"vertical-align: 0px;"> square feet! The linear conversion r=
atio of <img decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://spscc.pressbooks.pub/app/upl=
oads/quicklatex/quicklatex.com-69a7c7fb1023d315f416440bca10d849_l3.svg" cla=
ss=3D"ql-img-inline-formula quicklatex-auto-format" alt=3D"1" title=3D"Rend=
ered by QuickLaTeX.com" height=3D"12" width=3D"7" style=3D"vertical-align: =
0px;"> to <img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://spscc.pre=
ssbooks.pub/app/uploads/quicklatex/quicklatex.com-ce2009a45822333037922ccca=
0872a55_l3.svg" class=3D"ql-img-inline-formula quicklatex-auto-format" alt=
=3D"3" title=3D"Rendered by QuickLaTeX.com" height=3D"12" width=3D"9" style=
=3D"vertical-align: 0px;"> means that that the conversion ratio for the are=
as is <img decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://spscc.pressbooks.pub/app/uploa=
ds/quicklatex/quicklatex.com-69a7c7fb1023d315f416440bca10d849_l3.svg" class=
=3D"ql-img-inline-formula quicklatex-auto-format" alt=3D"1" title=3D"Render=
ed by QuickLaTeX.com" height=3D"12" width=3D"7" style=3D"vertical-align: 0p=
x;"> to <img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://spscc.press=
books.pub/app/uploads/quicklatex/quicklatex.com-a5e4c0fc0ad47996851c4f6d3e3=
ea7f6_l3.svg" class=3D"ql-img-inline-formula quicklatex-auto-format" alt=3D=
"3^2" title=3D"Rendered by QuickLaTeX.com" height=3D"15" width=3D"16" style=
=3D"vertical-align: 0px;">, or <img decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://spscc=
.pressbooks.pub/app/uploads/quicklatex/quicklatex.com-69a7c7fb1023d315f4164=
40bca10d849_l3.svg" class=3D"ql-img-inline-formula quicklatex-auto-format" =
alt=3D"1" title=3D"Rendered by QuickLaTeX.com" height=3D"12" width=3D"7" st=
yle=3D"vertical-align: 0px;"> to <img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" s=
rc=3D"https://spscc.pressbooks.pub/app/uploads/quicklatex/quicklatex.com-82=
4dc08b6ac6c7e5c07f1113ebaab27b_l3.svg" class=3D"ql-img-inline-formula quick=
latex-auto-format" alt=3D"9" title=3D"Rendered by QuickLaTeX.com" height=3D=
"12" width=3D"9" style=3D"vertical-align: 0px;">.</p>
<p>Here=E2=80=99s another way to think about it without a diagram: <img loa=
ding=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://spscc.pressbooks.pub/app/up=
loads/quicklatex/quicklatex.com-c799712baf211b805e4cb5ce2a139f59_l3.svg" cl=
ass=3D"ql-img-inline-formula quicklatex-auto-format" alt=3D"1\text{ yd}=3D3=
\text{ ft}" title=3D"Rendered by QuickLaTeX.com" height=3D"17" width=3D"82"=
 style=3D"vertical-align: -4px;">, so <img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"asy=
nc" src=3D"https://spscc.pressbooks.pub/app/uploads/quicklatex/quicklatex.c=
om-8116c757bf1c272057bed36740511885_l3.svg" class=3D"ql-img-inline-formula =
quicklatex-auto-format" alt=3D"(1\text{ yd})^2=3D(3\text{ ft})^2" title=3D"=
Rendered by QuickLaTeX.com" height=3D"20" width=3D"126" style=3D"vertical-a=
lign: -5px;">. To remove the parentheses, we must square the number <em>and=
</em> square the units: <img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" src=3D"htt=
ps://spscc.pressbooks.pub/app/uploads/quicklatex/quicklatex.com-7719dae4b24=
88219331fa3de0ca97806_l3.svg" class=3D"ql-img-inline-formula quicklatex-aut=
o-format" alt=3D"(3\text{ ft})^2=3D 3^2\text{ ft}^2=3D9\text{ ft}^2" title=
=3D"Rendered by QuickLaTeX.com" height=3D"21" width=3D"171" style=3D"vertic=
al-align: -5px;">.</p>
<p>More generally, we need to <strong>square</strong> the linear conversion=
 factors when converting units of area. If the linear units have a ratio of=
 <img decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://spscc.pressbooks.pub/app/uploads/qu=
icklatex/quicklatex.com-69a7c7fb1023d315f416440bca10d849_l3.svg" class=3D"q=
l-img-inline-formula quicklatex-auto-format" alt=3D"1" title=3D"Rendered by=
 QuickLaTeX.com" height=3D"12" width=3D"7" style=3D"vertical-align: 0px;"> =
to <img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://spscc.pressbooks=
.pub/app/uploads/quicklatex/quicklatex.com-ec4217f4fa5fcd92a9edceba0e708cf7=
_l3.svg" class=3D"ql-img-inline-formula quicklatex-auto-format" alt=3D"n" t=
itle=3D"Rendered by QuickLaTeX.com" height=3D"8" width=3D"11" style=3D"vert=
ical-align: 0px;">, the square units will have a ratio of <img decoding=3D"=
async" src=3D"https://spscc.pressbooks.pub/app/uploads/quicklatex/quicklate=
x.com-69a7c7fb1023d315f416440bca10d849_l3.svg" class=3D"ql-img-inline-formu=
la quicklatex-auto-format" alt=3D"1" title=3D"Rendered by QuickLaTeX.com" h=
eight=3D"12" width=3D"7" style=3D"vertical-align: 0px;"> to <img loading=3D=
"lazy" decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://spscc.pressbooks.pub/app/uploads/q=
uicklatex/quicklatex.com-e88489b836d3ea4c1e2c8d1f5576ce86_l3.svg" class=3D"=
ql-img-inline-formula quicklatex-auto-format" alt=3D"n^2" title=3D"Rendered=
 by QuickLaTeX.com" height=3D"15" width=3D"18" style=3D"vertical-align: 0px=
;">.</p>
<div class=3D"textbox textbox--exercises">
<header class=3D"textbox__header">
<p class=3D"textbox__title">Exercises</p>
</header>
<div class=3D"textbox__content">
<p class=3D"hanging-indent"><strong>1.</strong>&nbsp; An acre is defined as=
 the area of a <img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://spsc=
c.pressbooks.pub/app/uploads/quicklatex/quicklatex.com-80ac4a29199e9d2f97d2=
d19f5712c381_l3.svg" class=3D"ql-img-inline-formula quicklatex-auto-format"=
 alt=3D"660" title=3D"Rendered by QuickLaTeX.com" height=3D"12" width=3D"27=
" style=3D"vertical-align: 0px;"> foot by <img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D=
"async" src=3D"https://spscc.pressbooks.pub/app/uploads/quicklatex/quicklat=
ex.com-0929506a03694df24aee538b7f93fa1b_l3.svg" class=3D"ql-img-inline-form=
ula quicklatex-auto-format" alt=3D"66" title=3D"Rendered by QuickLaTeX.com"=
 height=3D"12" width=3D"18" style=3D"vertical-align: 0px;"> foot rectangle.=
 (That=E2=80=99s a furlong by a chain, if you were curious.) How many squar=
e feet are in <img decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://spscc.pressbooks.pub/a=
pp/uploads/quicklatex/quicklatex.com-69a7c7fb1023d315f416440bca10d849_l3.sv=
g" class=3D"ql-img-inline-formula quicklatex-auto-format" alt=3D"1" title=
=3D"Rendered by QuickLaTeX.com" height=3D"12" width=3D"7" style=3D"vertical=
-align: 0px;"> acre?</p>
<p class=3D"hanging-indent"><strong>2.</strong>&nbsp; How many square yards=
 are in <img decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://spscc.pressbooks.pub/app/upl=
oads/quicklatex/quicklatex.com-69a7c7fb1023d315f416440bca10d849_l3.svg" cla=
ss=3D"ql-img-inline-formula quicklatex-auto-format" alt=3D"1" title=3D"Rend=
ered by QuickLaTeX.com" height=3D"12" width=3D"7" style=3D"vertical-align: =
0px;"> acre?</p>
<p class=3D"hanging-indent"><strong>3.</strong>&nbsp; How many square inche=
s equals <img decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://spscc.pressbooks.pub/app/up=
loads/quicklatex/quicklatex.com-69a7c7fb1023d315f416440bca10d849_l3.svg" cl=
ass=3D"ql-img-inline-formula quicklatex-auto-format" alt=3D"1" title=3D"Ren=
dered by QuickLaTeX.com" height=3D"12" width=3D"7" style=3D"vertical-align:=
 0px;"> square foot?</p>
</div>
</div>
<p>It should be no surprise that this module will be full of conversion rat=
ios. As always, if you discover other conversion ratios that aren=E2=80=99t=
 provided here, it would be a good idea to write them down so you can use t=
hem as needed.</p>
</div>
<div>
<div class=3D"textbox shaded">
