</div>
<p>An acre is defined as a unit of area; it would be wrong to say =E2=80=9C=
acres squared=E2=80=9D or put an exponent of <img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=
=3D"async" src=3D"https://spscc.pressbooks.pub/app/uploads/quicklatex/quick=
latex.com-8c267d62c3d7048247917e13baec69a5_l3.svg" class=3D"ql-img-inline-f=
ormula quicklatex-auto-format" alt=3D"2" title=3D"Rendered by QuickLaTeX.co=
m" height=3D"12" width=3D"8" style=3D"vertical-align: 0px;"> on the units.<=
/p>
</div>
